OL,3,CNeighbour of train worker injured
OL,4,Cduring knife attack praises 'heroic'
OL,5,Cresponse
OL,7,FMr Zitouni has worked for LNER for
OL,8,Fmore than 20 years and was credited
OL,9,Fwith helping to save many lives after
OL,10,Fpassengers came under threat.
OL,12,FDavid Horne, LNER managing director,
OL,13,Fsaid: "In a moment of crisis, Sam did
OL,14,Fnot hesitate as he stepped forward to
OL,15,Fprotect those around him.
OL,17,F"His actions were incredibly brave,
OL,18,Fand we are so proud of him, and of all
OL,19,Four colleagues who acted with such
OL,20,Fcourage that evening.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/6
